=💤Description💤=
{{Blurimage|file=SleeplessDescription.jpg|caption=''entranced.''}}
A blue light cannot be ignored when in the belly of <b>57</b>. A harsh, yet incandescent blueish haze starkly permeates an otherwise pitch-black backdrop, providing the only source of illumination to the scene. Artificial light does not exist. This blue light paves the path for many emotions towards the unfortunate soul stuck in this paradise that was too good to be true, relaxation, nostalgia and an intangible tiredness only experienced by the heaviness of one's brows.

'''57''''s blue light is assisted by windows, spreading out the light into all the rooms that have one. Windowless rooms are so infrequent, that if it were said that they did not exist it would be taken as a fact. Even finding a white crow would be an easier task—ignoring the fact it's possible the crow was painted white. Past the window is a vast yet silent soviet cityscape that sleeps eternally, all the lights in the buildings turned off, nobody on the roads out. It truly does feel like you are alone, alone in your small yet ever-changing block.

The '''57''' level's appearance is quite simple. It is a small apartment, although it shifts and changes every now and then. There is one part that would stay, and that is the balcony. The balcony is small, yet it displays a different outdoor environment above the clouds, the stars shining and a crescent moon. Being there gives a feeling of being small; small compared to the greatness of stars.

During the generation of an apartment, a bedroom will always stay. If one is not on the balcony when it occurs, they will be put back in bed. Bathrooms, kitchens and living rooms can also appear.

While it is a basic skill, one may forget to sleep when in '''57'''. They won't get tired; it will just be the same relaxation and nostalgia the level traps someone in. The bad part is when they escape. They may have not slept for what would amount to twenty days outside—even if the effects are nullified when in your small apartment—they will all come crashing down at them if they escape. This leads to... rather undesirable outcomes when escaping.

