<nowiki>*********************************************************</nowiki>
<div class="lightblock>
Insomnia has been aching me. I find it hard to sleep nowadays. It might be stress or just being anywhere but in reality. I went through many sleepless nights in the span of maybe three or four days. I am already in a horrible mental state from my lack of sleep, or something else. “I will sleep tomorrow” I said to myself.

But an eternal tide still dragged me away. My dreams blossomed; an ocean empty yet full of every possibility. Although I cannot remember what my dream was, I remember it feeling real. When I woke up, I couldn't decide if it was reality or not. The simplest thing was to accept it as real as it slowly faded into a distant memory.

My internal monologue about whether the dream was true or false caused me to not realize I wasn't at the same level as before. It was somewhere else. 

Blue light shadowed every corner. The apartment was small. I felt the same as I felt during early mornings, where I woke up at five only for work. Or when I saw her. She was just a stranger I saw once. I still won't understand why I was so haunted and affected by it. It is best to look into the future. Thankfully, this place seems safe so far. Although you can't say for sure.

<nowiki>****</nowiki>

I think many months have passed since I arrived. Maybe years. I lost count when my apartment first changed. What even am I? Am I a ghost? Am I a mindless soul? I haven't eaten. I haven't drank. I haven't slept.

I looked into the corridor. My bones chilled, hardened as I saw…

her.

Why is she here? I saw her die… It is only her face, I think. It is just that her body is darkened under the blue light, or something else I couldn't comprehend. She didn't look real, yet looked real. I could almost see subtlety through her. 

She started moving. I had an urge to follow her.

In her path was a door. A door.

A door that wasn't there before.

It was red. Not painted, I could feel that it was made from red. Once finished it was painted over and over again, all the time with diffrent shades of red. The smell of paint was very strong. I opened it and went through.

<div class="onlydark"><div style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:1px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 1px; box-shadow: 0 0 10px white">
[[File:SleeplessHalls.jpg|500px|center|link=]]
</div></div>
<div class="onlylight"><div style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:1px solid #000000; border-radius: 1px; box-shadow: 0 0 10px black">
[[File:SleeplessHalls.jpg|500px|center|link=]]
</div></div>

A long tiled hallway waited after. Windows on the side, each with thin, almost paper-like curtains. Every few steps were sings, each reading "EXIT" in both English and a language I couldn't read. They didn't matter, I ran to the end of the corridor nonetheless.

At the end of the corridor was another door. The same red door as before. I looked behind myself. There was no sign of a red door—or a hallway. Only just a concrete wall that was way too close to me. I opened the door.

Was I walking towards my salvation or my demise? 

To my savior or my ender?

I stepped into an unkown, which looked unassuming. The same silent metropolis I saw every time I looked out the window. It was bathed in blue light, the same harsh blur light coming at me in my small conglomeration of rooms. I looked behind myself. The hallway disappeared, or the apartment. It disappeared without a trace.

What else was there was her. Right as she turned the corner. I could see her body now, although it was faded just enough I couldn't see details. I followed her.

Its odd. Every step I took, the more tired I got. I reached the corner where I saw her, yet there were no signs of her. The road was long, it must have been somewhere in the city center. She couldn't walk that fast.

I got tired, I can't keep up my pants. My legs feel like concrete and I fell to the ground. Came a sound I couldn't ignore.

Tires screaming.

Engines roaring.

A red car coming straight at me.  

It was unavoidable.  

Its tires will kiss my face.  

No pain came.  

It went through me.   

I floated past the car.   

I could see a weightless corpse, it's head crushed.

It was wearing my clothes.

It was mine.

It is clear now.

I remember.

She was never real.  

She was only in my dream.  

The dream that made me enter the level.  

And the many more who will.
